{
  "text": "Using CMs as a (mainly) permutation-based symmetric block cipher for visual data was introduced by Scharinger [CITATION_1] and Fridrich [CITATION_2] . CM encryption relies on the use of discrete versions of chaotic maps. The good diffusion properties of chaotic maps, such as the baker map or the cat map, soon attracted cryptographers. Turning a chaotic map into a symmetric block cipher requires three steps, as [CITATION_3] points out.",
